==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thraldom
<hw>Thral"dom</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Icel.
<ets><?/r⟦ae⟧ld⟦omac⟧mr</ets>. See <er>Thrall</er>, and
<er>-dom</er>.]</ety> <def>The condition of a thrall; slavery; bondage;
state of servitude.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>thralldom</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Women are born to <qex>thraldom</qex> and penance⟦br⟧
And to be under man's governance.</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He shall rule, and she in <qex>thraldom</qex> live.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thrall</ent>⟦br⟧
